## 7. Testing Strategy Updates

### New Test Targets

| Module | Test Type | Coverage Target |
|---|---|---|
| `media/capabilities.ts` | Unit | 100% |
| `media/encoder.ts` | Unit + Integration | 90% |
| `media/frameCapturer.ts` | Unit (mock Canvas) | 85% |
| `media/muxer.ts` | Integration | 80% |
| `timeline/timeline.ts` | Unit | 95% |
| `timeline/scheduler.ts` | Unit | 85% |
| `services/exportService.ts` | Integration | 85% |

### Testing WebCodecs in Vitest

WebCodecs is not available in Node.js. Two approaches:

1. **Mock strategy:** Create `__mocks__/webcodecs.ts` that stubs `VideoEncoder`/`VideoDecoder` with known byte outputs. Test the pipeline logic, not the browser codec.
2. **Playwright E2E:** Add Playwright tests that run in real Chrome for encoder integration tests. These run in CI only, not in `vitest run`.

